<section class="section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <article class="about-copy">
        <p>Each neighborhood has its own character, concerns, and priorities. WPCNA exists to help those neighborhoods stay connected to each other, to the city, and to what's happening across White Plains.</p>

        <p>This site is part of that effort. It's a simple, public guide to life in White Plains: events, meetings, local organizations, and the neighborhoods that shape the city.</p>

        <p>White Plains is the county seat of Westchester and a growing city with a busy downtown, a Metro-North connection to Grand Central, and a wide range of residential neighborhoods. Many of its residents work in New York City, and the city carries the energy and diversity you'd expect from a place with strong connections to both Westchester County and Manhattan.</p>

        <p>WPCNA itself is made up of representatives from neighborhood associations throughout White Plains. It serves as a forum for sharing information, raising concerns, and keeping communication open between neighborhoods and the broader community.</p>

        <p>If you're looking to get a better sense of what's happening in White Plains, you're in the right place.</p>
      </article>

      <div>
